It has the ability to accept a hand crank cocking device if you wish to install. Everything is stock except for the upgraded longer picatinny rail for mounting various sight combinations. I have a Trophy Winner Realtree soft case I will include with it along with the rope cocking device, sling, quick detach 3 bolt quiver, rail wax, scope, and three headhunter bolts. This is a serious crossbow, just because it's a zombie edition doesn't mean it's a toy. Specs are velocity 350FPS, draw weight 175lbs, kinetic energy 110 ft-lbs, 20" bolts 400-gr or heavier. Asking $450 can text more pics if requested.
